        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-11-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-11-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="657" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d657">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.6352/11–2745: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-11-27">November 27,
                            1945</date>.<lb/>[Received November 27—9:01 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1476. Local press recently carried stories with Washington datelines stating
                    definitely that United States official agencies would continue purchases of
                    Chilean copper at least through June 1946. Foreign Office has inquired whether
                    Embassy has received any confirmation. I should appreciate receiving urgently
                    any information throwing <pb facs="0823" n="809" xml:id="pg_809"/> light on this
                    situation which can appropriately be communicated to Chilean authorities.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bowers</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
